# Native pythoncm #

Native pythoncm is a replacement for the c++ wrapper library around libremotecm.so.
It is intended to have minimal prerequisites and run on python 2.7.5 or higher.

## Settings ##

The Settings class loads the url from: /var/spool/cmd/my.master.cmd.url
And uses the default user certificates in $HOME/.cm/admin.{pem,key}
Which should be the case for 90% of all applications.

Custom url, port, certificates can be specified

## Logging ##

Several kinds of logging are available:
* To file
* To stdout
* To null (default)

Optionally extra debug can be enabled

## Cluster ##

A cluster can be used in two modes:
* Fully connected, session, all entities (default)
* Unconnected, easy for making a few RPC calls (like prejob check)
